Wyoming.title: Unit Labor Costs for Private Nonfarm in Wyoming
Wyoming.notes: Unit labor costs represent the cost of labor required to produce one unit of output. The unit labor cost indexes are computed by dividing an index of nominal industry labor compensation by an index of real industry output.
